WHAT ARE RACIAL AND ETHNIC DISPARITIES?

Even when they have the same health insurance benefits and socioeconomic status, and when comorbidities, stage of presentation and other confounding variables are controlled for, members of racial and ethnic minority groups in the United States often receive lower-quality health care than do their white counterparts.
